{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1619059022,"nonce":"0zdoy60GJIdwaHURMZcOYM0f3qk=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU4NjQ0ODI5NjE=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3616","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhancement: NCBI SRA query tools should remove/ignore extra whitespace around accession IDs","message":"Tools: https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/tree/master/tools/sra-tools \n\nImpact: Any NCBI query tool that accepts accessions as input. These can be entered as individual accessions or a list of accessions (one per line). When whitespace is added to the tool form, or within a list, this causes the tools to fail. Trailing blank line(s) can also lead to avoidable failures. \n\nProposed fix: Strip any extra whitespace, empty newlines, or lines that contain only whitespace before making the query against NCBI. Any whitespace is not important to retain as far as I know, and cleaning up data seems like a practical \"make it easier to use\" change for these tools. Doesn't come up too often, but enough to address. **Papercut?**\n\nExample of the error in the command line for a failure:\n\n`acc='SRR1234567\t'`\n\nThanks for considering","files":null}]}